The authors argue that the Kirchhoff Braess paradox can pose a challenge for the operation of microgrids, which can be seen as a distributed computing problem. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the implications of the Kirchhoff Braess paradox for the operation of microgrids, which are an emerging technology in the field of power distribution.
